MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- instagram.py: add --write-comments to yt-dlp call; _first_owner_comment()
  finds the poster's own earliest comment and merges it into body_text with a
  "---" separator (skipped if identical to caption). Captures Axios/news-style
  posts that put the full article text in the first comment.

- prompts.py: add Geographic Overrides section — Charlotte, NC metro area
  content routes to SAVES/THINGS TO DO/{Restaurants|Bars|Events|...} instead
  of TRAVEL, with example paths and edge-case guidance.

- formatter.py: suppress post_title in frontmatter when it equals source_url
  (yt-dlp fallback when no real title was available).

https://claude.ai/code/session_01G3CevLYb6JPcyW363NyKGN
